main event: Witness observed oval, dark-colored objects flying from north to south at an altitude of 20-25,000 feet.
interesting points: Objects were larger than 2 inches and 7-8 inches thick., The flight was steady and the objects disappeared from sight., The sighting was made through ground visual observation., Witness used 18 power binoculars for observation., The sighting was reported in a Project Blue Book document.
witness description: Civilian, additional identifying information not provided.
